# ML-MLOps Production Template — Cursor Rules

## Critical Invariants

- NEVER use `uvicorn --workers N` in Kubernetes — 1 worker, HPA manages horizontal scale
- NEVER use memory as HPA metric for ML pods — CPU only
- ALWAYS use `asyncio.run_in_executor()` + `ThreadPoolExecutor` for CPU-bound inference
- ALWAYS use `KernelExplainer` for SHAP with ensemble/pipeline models (never TreeExplainer)
- ALWAYS use compatible release pinning (`~=`) for ML dependencies
- NEVER bake model artifacts into Docker images — use Init Container + emptyDir
- ALWAYS use IRSA (AWS) / Workload Identity (GCP) — no hardcoded credentials
- ALWAYS run quality gates (metric threshold, fairness DIR >= 0.80, leakage check) before promotion
- ALWAYS create an ADR for non-trivial architectural decisions

## Anti-Patterns (detect and correct)

- D-01: `uvicorn --workers N` → single worker + ThreadPoolExecutor
- D-02: Memory HPA → CPU-only HPA
- D-03: `model.predict()` in async endpoint → `run_in_executor`
- D-04: `shap.TreeExplainer` with ensembles → KernelExplainer
- D-05: `==` pinning → `~=` compatible release
- D-06: Unrealistically high metric → investigate leakage
- D-08: PSI with uniform bins → quantile-based bins
- D-09: Drift detection without heartbeat → add AlertManager alert
- D-11: Model in Docker image → Init Container pattern
- D-12: No quality gates → add all gates before deploy

## Code Style

- Python 3.11+ with type hints on all public functions
- Google-style docstrings
- black (line-length=120), isort (profile=black), flake8, mypy
- 90% line coverage, 80% branch coverage
- Compatible release pinning (`~=`) for all ML packages

## Stack

Python 3.11+, scikit-learn, XGBoost, LightGBM, FastAPI, Pandera, SHAP KernelExplainer,
Prometheus, Grafana, Evidently, MLflow, Docker, Kubernetes (GKE + EKS), Terraform, GitHub Actions, DVC

